---
import { markdownify } from "@/lib/utils/textConverter";
import CustomButton from "@/components/CustomButton.astro";
import OptimizedImage from "@/components/utilities/OptimizedImage.astro";
---

<section class="py-24 bg-white border-t-2 border-black">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
      <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
        <a href="/portfolio/reverse-engineering-sgo-success" class="block bg-white aspect-video border-2 border-black relative group hover:shadow-[8px_8px_0px_0px_rgba(0,0,0,1)] transition-shadow duration-300 overflow-hidden">
            <OptimizedImage 
                src="/images/portfolio/sgo-case-study.png" 
                alt="SGO Success Case Study" 
                class="w-full h-full object-cover"
            />
             <p class="absolute bottom-4 right-4 text-[10px] text-black font-mono font-bold uppercase tracking-wider bg-white px-1 border border-black">SGO Blueprint</p>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="order-1 lg:order-2 space-y-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold uppercase tracking-tighter leading-none text-black">
            Featured Work: <br/><span class="text-black decoration-4 underline decoration-[#00C853] underline-offset-4">Reverse Engineering SGO Success</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-black leading-relaxed font-mono">
          How does a legacy site maintain dominance in the AI-first search era? I reverse-engineered The Spruce Pets to uncover an "Authority-First" schema strategy that prioritizes trust signals and entity mapping for Google's AI Overviews.
        </p>
        <CustomButton label="Read SGO Strategy" url="/portfolio/reverse-engineering-sgo-success" class="btn-primary !border-2 !border-black !rounded-none hover:shadow-[4px_4px_0px_0px_rgba(0,0,0,1)] transition-shadow" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
